title.narrative: SOCIAL PROTECTION SYSTEM

description.narrative: Strengthened national and subnational capacity to develop and implement a child sensitive, inclusive and integrated social protection system, which contributes to Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Child poverty in all its forms is reduced through quality, evidence-based policies, programmes and budgets for all children, especially the most marginalized, at national and subnational levels

title.narrative: Strengthened national and subnational capacity to develop and implement a child sensitive, inclusive and integrated social protection system

description.narrative: The social protection agenda in Zanzibar continued to expand with universal pension and system development. However, the lack of political support for social protection in Tanzania Mainland presented significant challenges for policy and systems development. The new National Social Protection Policy was not submitted to Cabinet. At programme level, the Tanzania Social Action Fund (TASAF) Productive Social Safety Net (PSSN) programme discontinued payments to beneficiaries due to lack of funds. The approval of a new World Bank loan in September 2019 will facilitate resuming payments for PSSN under the second phase that starts in 2020. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:01/01/2020

title.narrative: 2.2 Policy/Strategy: Existence of valid national social protection strategy and/or policy

baseline.value: Mainland: Social Protection Framework (NSPF) is awaiting Cabinet approval. Zanzibar: Social Protection Policy (ZSPP) is in place (but not yet implemented).

target.value: 2021:Mainland: NSPF approved and fully operationalised. Zanzibar: ZSPP fully operationalised.

actual.value:
2020:The draft NSSP not approved. TOR for coordination and M&E framework developed.
ZSPP implementation progressively address issue of children – universal child grant and disability.
